&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a Band 5 Occupational Therapist to join our CARE point team for a 12 month contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated Occupational Therapist to join our Care Point Occupational Therapy team based at North Tyneside General Hospital. The successful candidate will be part of a multidisciplinary team who proactively facilitate a safe, effective and timely patient discharge and aim to prevent re-admission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; The applicant will be prepared to work weekends/bank holidays, and have a valid driving licence. The successful applicant must have excellent communication skills be able to work on their own initiative and as part of a team. We will provide access to reflective supervision, annual appraisals and professional development opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing Date: 15th November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
